graph.name: 128_pubchem_protein_toc
pubchem_description: This classification was created automatically from the PubChem Protein TOC on 2023/01/31.
Note that in some cases a number of highly populated nodes - those for which all or nearly all IDs have information - have been left out of the tree.
The sections, along with their child subsections, that are not shown in this tree are: Create Date, Modify Date, and Record Title.

nodes.name: 3D Structures
nodes.description: Experimental three-dimensional (3D) structures of a protein, determined through X-ray crystallography, NMR spectroscopy, etc.

nodes.name: AlphaFold Structures
nodes.description: Protein 3D structures, predicted by AlphaFold, an artificial intelligence (AI) system developed by DeepMind at Google. The image is generated by the iCn3D structure viewer developed at NCBI.

nodes.name: NCBI Protein Structures
nodes.description: Link to protein 3D structures from the NCBI Structure database, also known as the Molecular Modeling Database (MMDB).

nodes.name: PDB Structures
nodes.description: Protein 3D structures from the RCSB Protein Data Bank (PDB).

nodes.name: Sequence
nodes.description: Sequence of this protein in the FASTA format.

nodes.name: Domains
nodes.description: A protein domain is a region of a protein that can adopt a particular 3-D structure and usually performs a function.  Many proteins contain multiple domains, each of which is responsible for a particular function or interaction, contributing to the overall role of a protein.

nodes.name: CDD Domains
nodes.description: Protein domain annotation from the NCBI Conserved Domain Database (CDD).

nodes.name: Pfam Domains
nodes.description: Protein domain annotation from the Pfam database.

nodes.name: Biochemical Reactions
nodes.description: Biochemical reactions in which this protein/enzyme is involved

nodes.name: Glycobiology
nodes.description: Glycobiology is the study of the structure, biosynthesis, biology, and evolution of saccharides (sugar chains or glycans) that are widely distributed in nature in all living life forms.

nodes.name: Glycosylation
nodes.description: Glycosylation is the reaction in which a carbohydrate, i.e. a glycosyl donor, is attached to a hydroxyl or other functional group of another molecule (a glycosyl acceptor)

nodes.name: Patents
nodes.description: Patent applications/documents that mention this protein.

nodes.name: Biomarker Information
nodes.description: The term "biomarker", a portmanteau of "biological marker", is a measurable substance in an organism whose presence is indicative of some phenomenon such as disease, infection, or environmental exposure.

nodes.name: Interactions and Pathways
nodes.description: Interactions and pathways that involve this protein

nodes.name: Pathways
nodes.description: Biological pathways in which this protein is involved

nodes.name: Chemical-Protein Interactions
nodes.description: Interactions between chemcials and this protein

nodes.name: Interactions
nodes.description: Molecular interactions in which this protein is involved

nodes.name: Diseases and Phenotypes
nodes.description: Diseases and Phenotypes associated with this protein

nodes.name: Protein-Disease Associations
nodes.description: Diseases associated with this protein

nodes.name: BioAssays
nodes.description: Biological experiments deposited in PubChem BioAssay that were conducted against this protein.

nodes.name: Chemicals and Bioactivities
nodes.description: Drugs, chemical probes, curated ligands, and compounds tested against or related to this protein, along with associated bioactivity information.

nodes.name: Chemical Probes
nodes.description: Chemical probes developed by the Molecular Libraries Program (MLP) for this protein target, along with associated information.

nodes.name: Tested Compounds
nodes.description: Compounds tested against this protein in any bioassay deposited in PubChem.

nodes.name: Classification
nodes.description: Classifications and ontologies of this protein.

nodes.name: Enzyme Classification
nodes.description: Enzyme classification of this enzyme (a protein or the encoding gene) from ENZYME, an enzyme nomenclature database at the SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics.

nodes.name: NCI Thesaurus Tree
nodes.description: NCI Thesaurus (NCIt) hierarchy

nodes.name: MeSH Tree
nodes.description: The Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) tree for this entity.  MeSH is a controlled and hierarchically-organized vocabulary produced by the National Library of Medicine.

nodes.name: ChEMBL Target Tree
nodes.description: Classification of this entity in the context of targets, provided by ChEMBL.

nodes.name: IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY Target Classification
nodes.description: Classification of this entity in the context of targets, provided by the IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.

nodes.name: Literature
nodes.description: Scientific articles associated with this protein.  Some protein-literature associations in this section are provided by bioassay data contributors, while others are from curated resources, including DrugBank, and IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY, and UniProt.

nodes.name: BioAssay Provided PubMed Citations
nodes.description: PubMed citations provided by the bioassays associated with this protein.

nodes.name: DrugBank Interaction References
nodes.description: PubMed citations provided by DrugBank that are relevant to interactions with this protein.

nodes.name: Guide to PHARMACOLOGY Interaction References
nodes.description: Citations about interaction with this protein, provided by the IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.

nodes.name: UniProt References
nodes.description: PubMed citations associated with this protein, provided by UniProt (which is a popular resource for resource of protein sequence and functional information).

nodes.name: NLM Curated PubMed Citations
nodes.description: The NLM Curated PubMed Citations section links to all PubMed records that are tagged with the same MeSH term that has been associated with a particular protein.

nodes.name: Protein Information
nodes.description: General information about a protein

nodes.name: Enzyme
nodes.description: Enzyme Commission (EC) number for this protein. The EC number is a numerical classification scheme for enzymes, based on the chemical reactions they catalyze.  As a system of enzyme nomenclature, every EC number is associated with a recommended name for the corresponding enzyme-catalyzed reaction.

nodes.name: Encoding Gene
nodes.description: Gene that encodes this protein.

nodes.name: Record Description
nodes.description: Textual summary about this PubChem record

nodes.name: Taxonomy
nodes.description: Source organism of this protein.

nodes.name: Related Proteins
nodes.description: Related protein records in PubChem (e.g., orthologous proteins, similar-sequence proteins, same-gene proteins).

nodes.name: Orthologous Proteins
nodes.description: Proteins encoded by orthologous genes of different species, which evolved from a common ancestral gene.

nodes.name: Same-Gene Proteins
nodes.description: Proteins in PubChem encoded by the same gene of same species.

nodes.name: Sequence-Similar Proteins
nodes.description: Proteins in PubChem with similar sequence, which were identified by BLAST search using NCBI's non-redundant (nr) sequence database as background. The following thresholds were applied to define sequence similarity: coverage >= 60%, evalue <= 1e-6, and identity >= 60%

nodes.name: Names and Identifiers
nodes.description: Protein names, synonyms, and identifiers.

nodes.name: Other Identifiers
nodes.description: Other identifiers assigned to this protein.

nodes.name: ChEMBL Target ID
nodes.description: Target identifier used for this protein in ChEMBL.

nodes.name: DrugBank Target ID
nodes.description: Target identifier used for this protein in DrugBank.

nodes.name: Guide to PHARMACOLOGY Target ID
nodes.description: Target identifier used for this protein in the IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.

nodes.name: GlyCosmos Protein
nodes.description: Protein identifier used in GlyCosmos, a web portal for accessing glycoscience data from various web resources.

nodes.name: GlyGen Protein
nodes.description: Protein identifier used in GlyGen, a data integration/dissemination project for carbohydrate and glycoconjugate related data.

nodes.name: PRO ID
nodes.description: Identifier for this protein used in the Protein Ontology (PRO), which provides an ontological representation of protein-related entities by explicitly defining them and showing the relationships between them.

nodes.name: NCI Thesaurus Code
nodes.description: Stable, unique code for biomedical concept

nodes.name: Enzyme Commission (EC) Number
nodes.description: Enzyme Commission (EC) number for the enzyme encoded by this gene.  The EC number is a numerical classification scheme for enzymes, based on the chemical reactions they catalyze.  As a system of enzyme nomenclature, every EC number is associated with a recommended name for the corresponding enzyme-catalyzed reaction.

nodes.name: RefSeq Accession
nodes.description: Protein accession used in NCBI's Reference Sequence (RefSeq) database, which is an open-access, annotated, and curated collection of publicly available nucleotide sequences (DNA, RNA) and their protein products.

nodes.name: UniProt ID
nodes.description: Identifier for this protein assigned by UniProt, a popular resource containing protein sequence and functional information.

nodes.name: NCBI Proteins
nodes.description: NCBI Protein identifiers that are mapped to this protein target (e.g., proteins with identical sequence or mapped to the same UniProt record). These identifiers are provided by PubChem depositors.

nodes.name: Synonyms
nodes.description: Alternative names and abbreviations for this protein.

nodes.name: MeSH Entry Terms
nodes.description: Medical Subject Heading (MeSH) names or identifiers matching this protein.

nodes.name: Information Sources
nodes.description: Sources of annotation information attached to PubChem compounds
